Cycle.js

A functional and reactive JavaScript framework for predictable code

Website | Packages | Contribute | Chat | Support

## Welcome | Question | Answer | |--------|-------| | "I want to learn Cycle.js" | [Read the official documentation](https://cycle.js.org) | | "I have a question" | [Create a StackOverflow question](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/cyclejs)
Or
[Join the chat](https://gitter.im/cyclejs/cyclejs)
Or
[Open an issue](https://github.com/cyclejs/cyclejs/issues/new)
Please note all discussion-like issues are labeled discussion and immediately closed. This doesn't mean we unconsidered your discussion. We only leave actual issues open. | | "I found a bug" | [Open an issue](https://github.com/cyclejs/cyclejs/issues/new) | | "I want to help build Cycle.js" | [Read the Contributing guides](https://github.com/cyclejs/cyclejs/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md)
Then

releases.name: Not a major release, just a tiny breaking change
v0.24.1 - Introduce props.getAll() for custom elements
Drivers - new possibilities, breaking changes, but no breaking news
v0.21.2 - Tiny improvement: include svg() helper
v0.21 - This changes everything: one simple computer() function
v0.20.1 - Fix important and embarrasing bug
v0.20 - Streams: a dramatic breaking change
v0.18.2 - Custom elements can have nested vtrees
v0.18.0 - Small breaking change on DataFlowSink, plus improvements
v0.17.0 - View rejects custom element as root
v0.16.3 - Fix custom events from custom elements
v0.16.2 - Fix issue #89 with DOMUser and View
v0.16.0 - Breaking change to remove clone()
v0.15.3 - Fix Cycle's importability as an npm package
v0.15.0 - Small breaking change to custom elements
v0.14.4 - Fix glitch with lists of custom elements
v0.14.3 - Important consistency fixes to custom elements
v0.14.2 - Fix corner case bug for custom elements
v0.14.1 - Fix a bug in DOMUser classnames
v0.14.0 - Fix a bug with User.event$()
v0.13.0 Small breaking change to custom elements
v0.12.1 - Revolutionary breaking change in Views
v0.11.1 - Allows Renderer to target DocumentFragment
v0.11.0 - Simple breaking change to custom elements
v0.10.1 - Tiny fixes, and update virtual-dom
v0.10.0 - Minor fix to custom elements
v0.9.0 - Enable custom elements inside custom elements
v0.8.1 - Fix a bug in custom elements
v0.8.0 - Big breaking change to Views and DataFlowNodes
